---
// A real page so `/boom` resolves to a route (it has `routeData`). The request
// never reaches this template: src/middleware.ts throws for `/boom` first. This
// keeps `/boom` a middleware-throw case even when a prerendered 404.astro is
// present (which leaves unmatched routes with no `routeData`).
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head><meta charset="utf-8" /><title>unreachable</title></head>
	<body><p>unreachable - the middleware throws before this renders</p></body>
</html>
